<h2 id="partial-payment-on-july-1-by-using-the-settle-transactions-page">Partial payment on July 1 by using the Settle transactions page</h2>
<p>April can create a payment journal for this payment by opening the <strong>Payment journal</strong> page in Accounts payable. She creates a new journal and enters a line for vendor 3064. She then opens the <strong>Settle transactions</strong> page, so that she can mark the invoice for settlement. April marks the invoice and changes the value in the <strong>Amount to settle</strong> field to <strong>-500.00</strong>. She sees that the value in the <strong>Cash discount amount</strong> field is <strong>-10.00</strong> for the full invoice, and that the value in the <strong>Cash discount amount to take</strong> field is <strong>-5.05</strong>. Therefore, April is settling -505.05 of this invoice.</p>
